Mirth Corporation: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 5:39 PM ET
Health Care Technology

Company Overview of Mirth Corporation



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Mirth Corporation provides commercial and open source software and systems for health professionals in the United States. It offers Mirth Connect, a HL7 message integration product that provides the tools for developing, testing, deploying, and monitoring interfaces; Mirth Results that collects, organizes, and aggregates clinical data from various sources; and Mirth Match, an entity identification service for handling common healthcare Master Data Management patterns, such as Enterprise Master Patient Index, Master Provider Index, Facility index, or simple member list deduplication. The company also provides Mirth Mail, a directed exchange solution based on the NwHIN Direct specification and...
Mirth Corporation provides commercial and open source software and systems for health professionals in the United States. It offers Mirth Connect, a HL7 message integration product that provides the tools for developing, testing, deploying, and monitoring interfaces; Mirth Results that collects, organizes, and aggregates clinical data from various sources; and Mirth Match, an entity identification service for handling common healthcare Master Data Management patterns, such as Enterprise Master Patient Index, Master Provider Index, Facility index, or simple member list deduplication. The company also provides Mirth Mail, a directed exchange solution based on the NwHIN Direct specification and following an email paradigm that is accessed with various email clients; Mirth Care that allows healthcare provider organizations to harness patient data to engage patients and drive population health outcomes; and Mirth Appliances that offers a ready-to-run healthcare messaging platform. In addition, it offers VMware formatted virtual appliances; V1000-121 that integrates HIT application at a single healthcare provider organization to another application; V1000-12M for integrating HIE or EMR with multiple endpoints; and V1000-M2M for running a health information exchange or data aggregation hub with multiple participating organizations sending and receiving data through a common system. Further, the company provides services, such as channel report tool, Webinars, online tutorials, help desk, and developer Q and A; training; and consulting. It offers its solutions to healthcare organizations, such as HIEs, hospitals, clinics, laboratories, radiology, vendors, and government. Mirth Corporation was formerly known as WebReach, Inc. and changed its name to Mirth Corporation in April 2009. The company was founded in 1993 and is based in Irvine, California. As of September 9, 2013, Mirth Corporation operates as a subsidiary of Quality Systems Inc.
Detailed Description


